{
  "stem": "24346.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Our family tried to make us papers from the United States.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Americans wanted to liquidate the camps-- '48, say enough, let's give back the Germans the homes, and we'll take you to the United States.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we figured whichever comes first, we know we'll be candidates for the United States.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a couple.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a couple, because we already, were already married, and we had, already, a daughter.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our daughter that was born July the 9th, 1948.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they-- they announced, in 1948, that we're going to liquidate the camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had a baby girl, and we get-- so they took us to a camp that was so-called a temporary camp, till they call us to emigrate to the United States.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we went, I remember, the new camp, Kassel, near the city of Kassel.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a city-- the city of Kassel was bombarded a lot by the Allies, because they had their factories that made parts for airplanes.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they knew, the Americans, that without these parts, the plane cannot fly.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they bombarded these factories, they leveled them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But they created a camp near Kassel, a temporary camp till they called us to the United States.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there came at time in February, middle of February, that they called us, the office called us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They said, no more Kassel, now you're going to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We'll take you to a camp where we going to x-ray you and get you ready for the United States.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was in 1949.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Ma-- February of 1949, because I said we had to leave in 1948, Salzheim, and they took us to this temporary camp at Kassel.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So when they call us, when our papers get ready to be processed, they'll call us.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
